@startuml incident-sequence
title Resilience Scenario: Primary RabbitMQ Failure

participant "Outbox Processor" as OP
participant "PostgreSQL (Outbox)" as ES
participant "RabbitMQ (Broker)" as RMQ

activate OP
OP -> ES: Scan for new outbox events
ES --> OP: List of events (Event A, Event B)

OP -[#red]> RMQ: Try publish Event A
note right of RMQ: BROKER DOWN
RMQ -[#red]X OP: Connection Timeout/Error

note over OP: Retry Mechanism Triggered
OP -> OP: Wait (Exponential Backoff)

OP -[#red]> RMQ: Try publish Event A (Retry 1)
RMQ -[#red]X OP: Broker still unavailable

note over ES: Message remains in outbox as 'Unpublished'
note over ES: No data loss - persists in PostgreSQL

... Broker Recovers ...

OP -> RMQ: Try publish Event A (Retry 2)
RMQ --> OP: ACK (Success)

OP -> ES: Mark Event A as Published
ES --> OP: Success

note over OP: Idempotency Guard on Consumers\nprevents duplicate processing if ACK was lost.
deactivate OP

@enduml
